[1] Nigerian UN peacekeeper medevaced to Netherlands ex Liberia
Date: 6 Dec 2014
Source: Belfast Telegraph [edited]
http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/news/world-news/peacekeeper-in-liberia-tests-positive-for-ebola-virus-30803235.html


A UN peacekeeper in Liberia has tested positive for Ebola and will be flown to the Netherlands for treatment. The Nigerian soldier is expected to arrive in the Netherlands this weekend [6-7 Dec 2014] and will go into isolation at the University Medical Centre in Utrecht. It is the 3rd infection for the mission, which comprises about 7700 troops and police. The previous 2 cases were fatal. 16 people who came into contact with the Nigerian soldier have been quarantined, the mission said... - more

