[2] Cuba: doctor cured of Ebola goes home
Date: 7 Dec 2014
Source: Reuters [edited]
http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/reuters/article-2863350/Cuban-Ebola-patient-recovers-treatment-Geneva.html


A Cuban doctor who contracted Ebola in Sierra Leone and was cured after experimental treatment in a Swiss hospital vowed on Saturday [6 Dec 2014] to return to West Africa and continue treating patients. "I will finish what I started. I am returning to Sierra Leone," the doctor, 43, told reporters at Havana's Jose Marti airport shortly after landing, the official website Cubadebate reported. It was not immediately clear whether Cuban health officials would allow Baez to go back to Africa.

Cuba has won international praise for its contribution to fight the worst outbreak of Ebola on record, which has killed more than 6000 people. Some 200 doctors and nurses are on standby for an Ebola assignment in West Africa, in addition to the 256 already sent to Sierra Leone, Liberia and Guinea.

