[3] Canada: deploys medical team to Ebola-stricken Sierra Leone
Date: 6 Dec 2014
Source: CTV News Canada [edited]
http://www.ctvnews.ca/health/caf-deploys-medical-team-to-ebola-stricken-sierra-leone-1.2136407#ixzz3LDFiAQKq


The Canadian Armed Forces is sending a medical unit to Ebola-stricken Sierra Leone to help in the fight against the deadly virus. The team departed Canada on Sat [6 Dec 2014] morning bound for the U.K., where team members will participate in training before being deployed to the West African nation.

Ebola has hit Sierra Leone the hardest, with 1900 deaths as of Thu [4 Dec 2014]. The outbreak is now concentrated in some northern and western areas of the country, including the capital, Freetown.

[Byline: Michael Shulman]

